-- 
Columbia Names Mangurian Football Coach in Effort to End Losing Seasons

-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 
2011-12-08T16:06:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/columbia-names-peter-mangurian-football-coach-after-completing-1-9-season.html
Peter Mangurian was named football
coach at  Columbia University , the latest stop in a career that
includes previous time in the Ivy League and the  National
Football League , the school said today in an e-mailed release.  Mangurian, 56, is the 19th coach of the Lions, who were 1-9
this season and haven’t finished higher than fourth in the
eight-team Ivy League since 1996.  He succeeds Norries Wilson, who was fired after six seasons
and a 17-43 record at the New York-based university.  Mangurian was coach of  Cornell University  from 1998 to
2000, compiling a 16-14 record, according to the release. He
spent time as an assistant coach with the NFL’s Denver Broncos,
New York Giants, Atlanta Falcons,  New England Patriots  and Tampa
Bay Buccaneers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eben Novy-Williams in New York at 
